#578
The nest~
You have climbed into a large nest.  Logs the size of your thigh make up most
of the framework, with bear, elk, and wolf pelts stuffed into the cracks.
A large pile of bones is the only sign of occupation, but from the looks of
them you do not want to be around here when the owner is hungry.  As you look
around, you notice a second peak, much higher than this one.  There appears to
be no path to it, but there is a small cabin built on it.  I wonder who built it?
